recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2020-2022 Huracan EVO and 2022 Huracan STO vehicles.  The gearbox may have an insufficient amount of transmission oil, which can lead to clutch slippage, and in certain driving situations, a transmission oil leak.
recalls.Consequence: Clutch slippage can cause a loss of drive power and increase the risk of a crash.  A transmission oil leak in the presence of hot exhaust components can increase the risk of fire.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and correct the transmission oil level, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed May 20, 2022.  Owners may contact Automobili Lamborghini customer service 1-866-681-6276.  Automobili Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.02.22.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2022 Huracan EVO and STO vehicles.  The exterior driver-side door handle may not be assembled properly, which can prevent the opening of the driver-side door from the outside.
recalls.Consequence: A person may become trapped which, in the event of an emergency, may increase their risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the driver-side door handle, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 19, 2022.  Owners may contact Automobili Lamborghini customer service at 1-866-681-6276.  Automobili Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.03.22.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2015-2024 Huracan vehicles.  The headlights may be incorrectly adjusted.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Incorrectly adjusted headlights can reduce the visibility of oncoming traffic, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the software to deactivate the headlight functions for Tourist Mode and the Adaptive Front-lighting System (AFS), free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed February 6, 2024.  Owners may contact Lamborghini customer service at 1-866-681-6276.  Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.01.24.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Paint Issues
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly on the rear spoiler and side skirts, experiencing paint adhesion problems and clear coat peeling, especially on vehicles exposed to high temperatures or frequent washing
symptoms: Paint bubbling on carbon fiber parts
issues.fix_description: Professional repainting or carbon fiber panel replacement at authorized Lamborghini service center
issues.prevention: Avoid automatic car washes, use proper ceramic coating, park in covered areas when possible

issues.title: LDVI System Calibration Errors
issues.description: Lamborghini Dinamica Veicolo Integrata (LDVI) system showing calibration errors and failing to properly adjust suspension, steering, and traction control settings based on driving modes
issues.fix_description: Software update and sensor recalibration at dealership, possible sensor replacement
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid aggressive driving immediately after cold starts

issues.title: Exhaust Valve Actuator Failure
issues.description: Electronic exhaust valve actuators failing, causing exhaust valves to remain stuck in open or closed position, affecting sound and performance
symptoms: Exhaust note not changing with drive modes
issues.fix_description: Replacement of faulty exhaust valve actuators and related wiring
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance of exhaust system, avoid excessive idling

issues.title: Infotainment System Screen Flickering
issues.description: Central infotainment display experiencing intermittent flickering, blank screens, or complete system freezes, particularly during hot weather conditions
issues.fix_description: Infotainment system software update or display unit replacement
issues.prevention: Keep vehicle in shaded areas, ensure proper ventilation, regular software updates

issues.title: Front Splitter Damage from Normal Driving
issues.description: Front carbon fiber splitter experiencing damage from normal road conditions due to extremely low ground clearance, including scraping on driveways and speed bumps
issues.fix_description: Replacement of damaged carbon fiber splitter components
issues.prevention: Use front axle lift system, careful navigation over obstacles, consider protective films

issues.title: Brake Disc Warping Under Track Use
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brake discs showing premature warping and cracking under heavy track use, despite being designed for high-performance applications
issues.fix_description: Replacement of carbon ceramic brake discs and potentially brake pads
issues.prevention: Proper brake cooling procedures on track, avoid aggressive braking when brakes are cold

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Sticking
issues.description: Electronic door handles experiencing sticking or delayed response, particularly in cold weather conditions or after extended periods without use
issues.fix_description: Lubrication and adjustment of door handle mechanism, potential actuator replacement
issues.prevention: Regular use of vehicle, keep handles clean and dry, park in heated garage when possible

issues.title: Rear Wing Actuator Malfunction
issues.description: Active rear wing experiencing actuator failures, causing the wing to remain in fixed position or move erratically, affecting aerodynamic performance
symptoms: Wing stuck in raised or lowered position
issues.fix_description: Replacement of rear wing actuator motor and recalibration of system
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning of wing mechanism, avoid manual manipulation of wing

editorial.hero_blurb: The Huracán Tecnica strikes the perfect balance between the hardcore STO and the comfort-focused EVO. It's a naturally aspirated V10 masterpiece that delivers genuine supercar thrills without the compromises.
editorial.essence: This is Lamborghini's sweet spot - a rear-wheel-drive weapon that maintains the soul of the iconic V10 while offering surprising usability. The Tecnica represents the purest expression of what a modern Huracán should be.
editorial.heritage: Born from the Gallardo's legacy and refined through a decade of Huracán evolution, the Tecnica incorporates lessons learned from the track-focused STO while maintaining the accessibility that made the Huracán Lamborghini's bestseller.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers focused on creating aggressive aerodynamic functionality without sacrificing everyday usability, resulting in a car that looks purposeful from every angle while remaining approachable for regular driving.
editorial.motorsport_history: Draws directly from Lamborghini's Super Trofeo racing series and GT3 competition programs, incorporating aerodynamic lessons and chassis tuning developed on professional racing circuits.
editorial.engine_character: The 5.2L V10 is an absolute masterpiece - linear power delivery that builds to a crescendo at 8,500 RPM with none of the lag or artificial enhancement of forced induction. It's raw, immediate, and emotionally engaging.
editorial.transmission_feel: The seven-speed dual-clutch fires off shifts with military precision in Corsa mode, yet remains smooth enough for traffic in Strada. Paddle responses are instantaneous with satisfying mechanical feedback.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Rear-wheel-drive configuration allows for genuine tail-happiness when provoked, while advanced electronics provide a safety net. The chassis communicates beautifully, telegraphing grip levels and balance shifts through the seat.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic-assisted steering delivers authentic road surface feedback without being twitchy. Weight builds naturally with speed, and the car responds immediately to inputs with surgical precision.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon-ceramic brakes provide massive, fade-free stopping power with excellent pedal feel. Initial bite is strong but progressive, inspiring confidence on both road and track.
editorial.sound_signature: Pure automotive symphony - the naturally aspirated V10 produces a complex harmony that builds from a purposeful rumble to a spine-tingling wail that hits stratospheric notes near redline.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who want authentic supercar experience with modern reliability, weekend track warriors who also need a car for special occasions, and enthusiasts who prioritize engine character over ultimate lap times.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Comfort-first buyers seeking luxury touring capability, those who prioritize straight-line acceleration over handling finesse, or drivers who rarely explore the upper rev range.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Tecnica represents the best of both worlds - genuine supercar performance with surprising daily usability. Focus on low-mileage examples with complete service records, and don't overlook the importance of proper pre-purchase inspection.
pros: Perfect balance of performance and usability
cons: Can be challenging in wet conditions
